<COURSE coursename="All Lines Insurance  :- Beginning" status="3" coursetype="2" courselevel="2" description="This course was designed for those busy professionals seeking an adjuster&apos;s license in the comfort of their own environment.  This ALL LINES Texas license will allow the adjuster to adjust everything known to mankind. Please note this license assures that all candidates are LEGAL to adjust everything known to mankind however, this course does not assure the adjuster&apos;s competency to adjust those items. This will be accomplished through post licensing education. The Texas license is also known as the &quot;gateway license&quot; throughout the adjusting industry. Once Texas licensed, the adjuster can use their Texas license to receive up to 40 other states license WITHOUT ADDITIONAL TESTING (by simply paying a fee &amp; completing state licensing forms). Ask our rep. for more info. This course covers the mandated TDI topics: TSFP, Auto Ins., Personal &amp; Commercial Lines, Ocean &amp; Inland Marine, Prof. Coverages, Surety Bonds, Adj. Terms &amp; Def., Adj. duties &amp; various Consumer Protection issues." language="English" courselength="600" coursedate="4/5/2007" ispaid="1" price="0" grp="1284" seq="1" passinggrade="70" rating="6" ratingcnt="54" classes="71" video="0" audio="0" quiz="1" reference="" scorefactor="1" nocertificate="1" noevaluation="1" iscustomcertificate="1">
<DESCRIPTION><!--  
<P align=center><META content="MSHTML 6.00.2800.1400" name=GENERATOR><B><U><FONT size=3>Knowledge, Skills, Abilities this course will provide for all students</FONT></U></B> 
<P align=justify><B><U><I>This course will provide the TDI mandated curriculum&nbsp;required for this license.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Plus,&nbsp; the student will be able to ...</I> 
<BR></U></B>Understand each "TEXAS" specific policy form, <I>including;</I> Texas Standard Fire Policy (TSFP),Texas Personal&nbsp;Auto Policy (PAP), Texas Personal Lines coverage including;&nbsp;HO A/B/C Renters/Condo, Commercial Lines coverage's, Inland and Ocean Marine, as well as, Additional Coverage’s for Today’s Busy Professionals,&nbsp;&amp; Surety Bonds. Plus, this course includes "Adjusting Terminology" &amp; The TDI rules pertinent to maintaining and renewing the adjuster license including; Fines, Fees, etc. Finally, the course reviews Consumer Protection rules and The Texas Worker's Compensation Act. 
<P align=justify><B><U><I>This course will provide the skills each candidate needs in order to...</I> 
<BR></U></B>Distinguish between each policy's benefits, including; the exclusions, conditions &amp; endorsements particular to each policy form.&nbsp; in addition, each student will learn important industry language used daily in his or her new profession.&nbsp; Plus, each candidate will be required to complete many case study dilemmas in order to pass the final examination while applying policy limits, exclusions, etc. to particular question so they may determine the proper answer while obtaining a minimum of a 70% score overall on the final examination. 
<P align=justify><B><U><I>This course will assure the candidates have the ability to…</I> 
<BR></U></B>Act as the liaison between the parties of interest: The Insurer, The Insured and The Claimant.&nbsp; To be aware that an adjuster who does their continuing education hours after their expiration date could face fines of $1,500 per renewal period.&nbsp; As will as, licensing violation fines, cease and desist order fines and Fair Housing Act violation and fines imposed by the governing agency!&nbsp; Plus, the candidate will be armed with the ability to figure the insurers and insured’s obligations, duties, policy obligations and rights, etc. 
<P align=justify>Our goal for all adjuster’s attending our course is to greatly increase the communication in respect to claims handling between The Insurer and The Insured, while restoring public respect regarding insurance as a whole.&nbsp; Also, this course is considered a licensing course that will greatly increase the student’s intelligence and professionalism to help with claims conflict resolution, expediency in paying claims that are legitimate.&nbsp; Plus, understanding Fraud Indicators that arise more often than not in various types of claims processing.&nbsp; Finally, this course will address Marketing Do’s and Don’ts and Workers Compensation information relative to Texas claimants. 
<BR>&nbsp; 
<P><B>Approval Number:</B> 
<P>&nbsp; 
<P><B>Category:</B> 
<P><B>Pre-Licensing Educational Course Texas All Lines Adjusters License</B> 
<P><B>Regulatory Requirement:</B> 
<P>The course was approved by TDI for 10 hours of home study and 30 hours of classroom equivalent study to equal the required 40 hours of mandated curriculum.&nbsp; The student must acknowledge that they have studied the 10 hours of home study based on the honor system (and may print the textbook at their leisure). After agreeing with the acknowledgement statement the student will review the remaining curriculum over the internet.&nbsp; Each&nbsp;hour of course study consist of the following;&nbsp;Two pages of materials, a section scenario and&nbsp;an inquiry period&nbsp;which consist of&nbsp;four questions over the materials reviewed within the particular section. Upon completing the inquiry period the score over the&nbsp;four questions will be revealed ( must be a minimum of 75% or 3 out of the four correct to move forward). If the student does not choose the correct answer.&nbsp; The correct answer and an explanation as to why the answer is correct will be provided.&nbsp; The&nbsp;student must master the inquiry period with a minimum score of&nbsp;75%&nbsp;in order to move to the next&nbsp;section. However, if the student does not pass the section with the required minimum score the student may study the materials at their leisure before taking the inquiry questions again or simply go directly to taking another verison of questions for the related section. The student must show mastery throughout the required lessons in this course in order to be eligible to take the final exam required by TDI. 
<P>Upon successful mastery of each lesson the student is now able to choose their monitor. A monitor is defined as; anyone not related to the student by blood, marriage, etc.&nbsp; Plus, the monitor cannot supervise the student as well as, the student cannot supervise the monitor.&nbsp; The monitor will be required to sign the affidavit (which will be available for printing with forwarding instructions on the form) and our home office staff must have this signed form before the certificate of completion can be mailed to the student.&nbsp; 
<P><B> Testing:</B>  
<P>The final examination consist of 150 questions multiple choice.&nbsp; Each question was taken directly from the course materials and we assure the student that the materials are covered within the course curriculum.&nbsp; The student has 180 minutes (3 hours) in which to take the exam. We have added a clock to assist you while taking the exam.&nbsp; Any questions not answered of the 150 questions within the allotted timeframe will be considered wrong in the final grading.&nbsp; Upon completion we will provide an immediate pass of fail grade for the student.&nbsp; The student must receive a 70% or higher on the final exam (105 correct or the student may miss 45 questions).
<P><B>Course Pre-Requisite:</B> 
<P><B> The student is not required to have prior knowledge in the field of adjusting in order to successfully pass this course and receive their certificate.</B> 
<P><B>Course Completion:</B> 
<P><B>In order for a successful completion the student must complete the course lessons and home study hours before being eligible to take the final exam.&nbsp; The final exam is closed book at all times and requires a monitor affidavit.&nbsp;&nbsp; Upon receipt of all required information by our home office staff we will mail your certificate of completion within 30 days from completion of all required items&nbsp;to the address indicated in your personal profile.&nbsp; NOTE: F0R THOSE STUDENTS THAT NEED AN IMMEDIATE LICENSE OR WOULD LIKE TO ELIMINATE AN ADDITIONAL FOUR WEEKS WAITING PERIOD BETWEEN COMPLETION AND TDI SUBMISSION OF REQUIRED DOCUMENTS IN ORDER TO OBTAIN THEIR LICENSE FROM TDI... WE NOW OFFER THE EXPRESS SERVICES WHICH WILL EXPEDITE YOUR CERTIFICATE OF COMPLETION TO BE FAXED&nbsp; WITHIN 24 BUSINESS HOURS OF COMPLETION OR THE SERVICE IS FREE BY OUR HOME OFFICE STAFF. SIMPLY CHOOSE THIS PROCESS BEFORE SUBMITTING THE INFORMATION TO US FOR FINALIZATION</B>
<P><B>Course Instructor Information:</B> 
<P>This course was developed by Sheila Trussell.&nbsp; Ms. Trussell has been serving the Insurance industry since 1984.&nbsp; She began offering and instructing Continuing Education courses throughout the nation in 1992.&nbsp;   --></DESCRIPTION>
